IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Assuring Help for the World's Most Vulnerable People.
IRS990.MissionDescription: Global Impact's mission is to assure help for the world's most vulnerable people. Since its inception in 1956, Global Impact has generated more than $1.3 billion to help people in need. By creating results-driven giving opportunities for donors and partners through trusted efficient giving programs, Global Impact's funded charities touch more than 400 million lives each year through disaster relief, education, health care, training and economic programs that promote self-sufficiency, strengthen communities and offer hope by raising funds in nearly 500 workplace giving programs on behalf of 55 of the most respected international charities; managing the two largest combined federal campaigns with assistance of thousands of federal workers, about 250,000 donors and receipt of $82.2 million in pledges; distributing funds raised in 15 corporate workplace giving programs to nearly 9,000 charities; and developing innovative public private partnerships to address needs in new ways.
IRS990.Description: Managed Campaigns - The Combined Federal Campaign is a workplace giving program created for Federal workers. It is the largest charity effort of its kind in the world. Global Impact manages the campaign in the Washington, DC area and the campaign for men and women in the Department of Defense serving overseas. During this past year, both campaigns once again reached new records in giving. The Combined Federal Campaign of the National Capital Area raised $66.5 million in the fall 2009 campaign. That is an unprecedented growth of 31 percent during the last seven years under Global Impact's direction. Donors in the Combined Federal Campaign-Overseas gave $15.7 million in the fall 2009 campaign, a 111 percent increase since Global Impact began managing the campaign in 1996. This statistic takes on special significance because donors include thousands of military personnel deployed to Iraq and Afghanistan who are already making enormous personal sacrifices through their service to our country. Donors in the two campaigns increased their giving by $3.6 million to help people in need, accounting for 57 percent of all new funds raised nationwide by 226 CFCs last year.

Activity2.Description: Distribution Services (Donor Advised Funds) - Global Impact adheres to a rigorous series of checks and balances that ensure transparency and sound financial management. External audits confirm the success of these practices, year after year. Global Impact received the Charity Navigator Four-Star Rating, for the sixth consecutive year, as well as the Seal Holder status from the Better Business Bureau Wise Giving Alliance, for the fifth consecutive year.With these excellent ratings, sixteen Fortune 500 corporations selected Global Impact to distribute funds as part of their workplace giving campaigns. These partnerships delivered $14.3 million to 9,000 charities serving people around the world.

Activity3.Description: Workplace Giving - Global Impact raises funds for its alliance of 56 U.S.-based international charities through innovative partnerships and giving programs in the workplace. Each of these charities is thoroughly vetted annually and has a proven track record of success in promoting self-sufficiency, strengthening communities and offering hope. Through the efforts of Global Impact, these charities participate in approximately 500 workplace campaigns conducted by across the full spectrum of public sector and private sector organizations. By streamlining the processes for both the collection and distribution of funds and lists of donors, Global Impact helps reduce administrative costs and provides an effective path to its charities for raising greater revenue. Additionally, Global Impact raises money for disaster relief, mostly through corporate partners who work with Global Impact because of the efficiency and effectiveness of their campaigns. During this year, Global Impact raised $600,000 through such campaigns on behalf of Haiti.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 4
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: During fiscal 2010, both the Articles of Incorporation and the By-Laws were amended to create two classes of charities, full member and associate member. Full members have the right to vote on certain matters of governance, while associate members do not have the right to vote. This change furthers Global Impact's mission by allowing it to raise money on behalf of a wider circle of charities.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Form 990 is reviewed by the chair of the Audit Committee prior to a board meeting. The form is presented to the Board by the Audit Committee chair. Each board member then receives by email an electronic version of the form, so that each can review it and raise questions before the form is filed.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A yearly signing of conflict of interest is done by all members of the board and staff.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The board chair and independent members of the board make decisions during Executive Session. Comparative compensation data for the President and CEO is provided to the Chairman of the Board by the Chief Financial Officer and the Director of Human Resources. This information is considered by the independent members of the Board, who are charged with approving the salary of the President and CEO as well as any performance bonus. Similar comparative compensation information is provided to the President and CEO to help guide decisions about other key employees.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy, and financial statements available to the public upon request.
There have been no changes during the year in the process for oversight of the audit of the financial statements.
